<Author>tenpepper
<Content>Worst Stay Ever at the Atlantic Beach Hotel It was my first stay in the Condado area and it being a short weekend trip I wanted to be on the beach. Therefore, I left a much nicer, yet less expensive hotel a block away to be at the Atlantic Beach Hotel. Within minutes of checking in, my wallet, credit cards and all indentification cards were stolen from me in the middle of the day near the bar area of the hotel. It is not that I hold the hotel responsible for this (however, one would like to think that he/she was safe at the hotel), I got absolutely no assistance from them and had to seek out the police to file a report on my own (not that they were anymore concerned than the Atlantic Beach management and staff). Luckily the hotel had secured a credit card hold for my room. And although they had secured a much higher limit than the rooom rate, they absolutely refused to add a incidental (taxi fare) to the room charge to get me back to the airport. Basically I was stranded and it was the hotel's attitude and lack of concern that bothered me, especially since the theft took place on their property. The next morning when I did check out and tried again to get the hotel to add the incidental (taxi fare) to the ticket before it was closed out, the lady would not, nor would she call the manager to get apporval to do it. When she gave me their copy of my room charges for me to sign, I wrote on it that my credit cards, money and ID's had been stolen while staying there. The lady got furious at this and started yelling. After being told that the room had been billed successfully to my credit card, I had had enough of the Atlantic Beach Hotel and staff. I left without being given a copy of my room charges. It was my decision to leave a better hotel a block away to stay at the Atlantic Beach Hotel. And if it had not been for the theft, I would have accepted everything, even the extremely small, poor condition, over-priced rooms and would have had a good time! It's just the NO-CARE attitude from the management toward their guests is bothersome. One other issue I had was trying to get back up to my room as guests have to be buzzed back in. However, the desk staff were never at the desk and were out on the street talking to other people. Once inside, I felt like I was in a high school dorm on lockdown as guest are not allowed upstairs. You can not despute that the hotel is in a great location and that the bar area is fun and that the barbacks are the BEST. Nevertheless, I would recommend to anyone that they stay at another of the many hotels in the area and experience the Atlantic Beach Bar without staying at the hotel !!! Lessons learned ...and I learned the hard way! 
<Date>Dec 1, 2008
