<Content>Party Central for San Juan Gay Life, (By Day and By Night) I had a fantastic time in San Juan and the Atlantic Beach Hotel is the focal point of everything during my stay. First, the people are great, from the bar staff, (and yes, I spent a lot of time here), to the front desk, security, and house keeping, the people make it so much fun. This was my third visit here over the last five years and Terri has really turned the staff around here, much improved over what it was when he took over the establishment. Terri has taken a very hands on interest in the place and is there every day and night to see that his guests are satisified. He is remodelling roomes and the hotel. It is a big project but progress is being made in every corner. There are other alternatives in the area but this is party central, it is all about convenience. You can walk from the bar to your room when you need something or have that visitor that wants to see what your room looks like. The bar is active seven days a week, party central and the starting point for every evening. And, YES, you can bring visitors up to the rooms. The security and hotel staff do filter out the problematic people but if the guest does not have a history or it is an obvious problem person, they are there to protect you. They welcome you to have a guest up to your room. Don't go by what you have heard in the past, this place is party central and is getting better every day. Thanks to Terri and his entire staff. Jim 
