<Content>Clean  If you are expecting the Ritz.. find somewhere else to go. My friend (25yo)and I (23yo) spent the New Year at the Atlantic Beach and we had a great time for the week we were there. The front desk staff is semi friendly.. the bar was great times  the bartenders are fun as well.. you just have to make an effort to be personable and get to know the guys (you just can't sit there! Be sociable!).Upon check-in everything was great and we were buzzed in and then we got into the Crickity  somewhat scarry elevator which took us to our room. The room was clean and similar to what you would get at Super 8. The view was fantastic and so was the one from the top sun deck.Okay.. lets do the pros  cons:Pros- Location, Bar, Beach steps away, View, Clean Rooms, AtmosphereCons- Older building, the Elevator, Waiting for Hot Water (run the shower for about 5 min before getting in), lack of storage in rooms.Previous posts on here say some of the worst things.. but honestly people.. this is a great place to stay due to its location and atmosphere. Overall quality is okay... if I were to go back to PR, I would probably stay @ the Atlantic again.(Tips for PR: If you are up for taking the bus.. its only 25cents to Old SanJuan.. Taxi is approx $12 eachway. Also, the shops in OSJ close EARLY !) Most of all have fun  enjoy your trip.. I know we did! 
