<Content>I was very pleased with my stay. I have been visiting an Juan, Puerto Rico for the past fifteen years. and have stayed numerous times at the Atlantic Beach hotel over the years.Although it had been two years since my last visit to San juan and the Atlantic Beach, I decided to give the Hotel and its new management a try despite some of the negative reviews that had been posted all over the internet.I was truly surprised, and pleased at the experience I had encountered during my ten-day stay. What I experienced was a completely transformed gay-frinedly hotel with a much different environment from which I had previously experienced on my visits over the past 15 years.The first thing I noticed upon arriving was that all of the hustlers (drug addicts) who used to surround the area 24 hours a day (streets, gay beach, Barefoot Bar, etc...) as well a inside the rooms and bar of the Atlantic Beach had disappeared entirely. The new management has apparently restricted their entrance to the property so they have all vanished or moved on to other areas outside the Condado.During my stay, there were numerous old local friend who I had met on previous visits to Puerto Rico, as well as some new aquaintances that the hotel staff and management said were more than welcome to visit me in my room. However, they made it quite clear that the hutlers were not permitted anywhere on the premises, if that was my intentions. This new policy made me feel something that I had never felt before during my previous stays at the Atlantic Beach - safe and secure.Along with a definitely more friendly management and staff, I noticed a much cleaner, organized and upgraded hotel accomadations which appeared to be an ongoing project.I must say that the new management and staff has created one of the most charming, friendly, fun and safe hotels in all of puerto Rico. I will definitely return very soon. 
